6. adulescentulum. On the u with which the word should be spelt, see Ritsohl Proleg. ad Trin. p. xcv.

As to the allusion we know nothing. Terence’s literary taste disdained any approach to burlesque. Perhaps some such stripling as the Menaechmus of Plautus (as Wagner sug- gests) is intended.

7. sectari. Frequentative verbs are especially frequent in the comic poets: sometimes stronger than the primary verb, sometimes not. Cf. e.g. infr. 34, 99.
